On Night 2 of their convention, Democrats delivered to Mr. Biden a prize he has pursued intermittently since 1988, in a triumph of endurance for him.The roll call vote showcased the cultural diversity of Democrats’ coalition and exposed a generational gulf that is increasingly defining the party.
Night 2 of the convention focused on how much work awaits the next president, and the reasons Democrats think voters should trust Mr. Biden with the job.
Speaking in the border city of Yuma, Ariz., President Trump boasted about his own efforts to sharply limit immigration during his time in office.
Mr. Clinton issued a blistering attack on President Trump at the first Democratic convention since the 1980s where he is little more than a bystander.
In a procedural move, Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez nominated Senator Bernie Sanders, a fellow democratic socialist, for the presidency.
President Trump and President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia at the Group of 20 summit in Japan last year. Erin Schaff/The New York Times

Senate Report Examines Possible Compromises in Trump Trips to RussiaPresident Trump may have had a relationship with a former Miss Moscow, the report said, but investigators “did not establish” that Russia had compromising information.
A Senate Intelligence Committee report details Paul Manafort’s ties to a Russian agent during the 2016 election.

The University of North Carolina moved classes online, but sports will continue, for now.

Joe Biden Is Officially Designated as Democratic Nominee for PresidentOn the second night of their convention, Democrats rewarded Mr. Biden with the formal nomination he has pursued intermittently since 1988.The roll call vote showcased the cultural diversity of their coalition and exposed a generational gulf that is increasingly defining the party.
Watch the four moments that mattered on the D.N.C.’s second night.

In Speech, Jill Biden Addresses Pandemic Concerns About EducationDr. Biden, who worked as a full-time professor at a community college even while serving as second lady, spoke to the challenges educators are facing.

Analysis: Changed World, Same Biden Seeking to Undo What Trump Has DoneThe convention focused on how much work awaits the next president, and the reasons Democrats think voters should trust Joe Biden with the job.
Hillary Clinton’s Bittersweet Return to the StageMrs. Clinton sees her appearance as an opportunity to harness the feminist movement that grew out of her loss and to eject President Trump from power.

Who Spoke Most on Night 2 of the Democratic National Convention?Jill Biden had nine minutes, Bill Clinton had about five, and Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez a minute and half. Here’s how the virtual event’s air time played out.

G.O.P.-Led Senate Panel Details Ties Between 2016 Trump Campaign and RussiaA nearly 1,000-page report confirmed the special counsel’s findings at a moment when President Trump’s allies have sought to undermine that inquiry.
Here are eight takeaways from the Senate Intelligence Committee’s report.
The report details Paul Manafort’s ties to a Russian agent during the 2016 election.
